#. VAR: Evaṃmāni → evaṃ mānī (bj, pts1, mr) | evamādi (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn105:18.4"
msgid "Evaṃmāni assa atathaṃ samānaṃ. "
msgstr "Having such conceit, though it’s not based in fact, "

msgctxt "mn105:18.5"
msgid "So yāni sammā nibbānādhimuttassa asappāyāni tāni anuyuñjeyya; asappāyaṃ cakkhunā rūpadassanaṃ anuyuñjeyya, asappāyaṃ sotena saddaṃ anuyuñjeyya, asappāyaṃ ghānena gandhaṃ anuyuñjeyya, asappāyaṃ jivhāya rasaṃ anuyuñjeyya, asappāyaṃ kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ anuyuñjeyya, asappāyaṃ manasā dhammaṃ anuyuñjeyya. "
msgstr "they would engage in things unconducive to extinguishment: unsuitable sights, sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and thoughts. "

msgctxt "mn105:18.6"
msgid "Tassa asappāyaṃ cakkhunā rūpadassanaṃ anuyuttassa, asappāyaṃ sotena saddaṃ anuyuttassa, asappāyaṃ ghānena gandhaṃ anuyuttassa, asappāyaṃ jivhāya rasaṃ anuyuttassa, asappāyaṃ kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ anuyuttassa, asappāyaṃ manasā dhammaṃ anuyuttassa rāgo cittaṃ anuddhaṃseyya. "
msgstr "Doing so, lust infects their mind, "

msgctxt "mn105:18.7"
msgid "So rāgānuddhaṃsitena cittena maraṇaṃ vā nigaccheyya maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ. "
msgstr "resulting in death or deadly pain. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya19, pts-vp-pli2.257, sc11
msgctxt "mn105:19.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, sunakkhatta, puriso sallena viddho assa savisena gāḷhūpalepanena. "
msgstr "Suppose a man was struck by an arrow thickly smeared with poison. "

msgctxt "mn105:19.2"
msgid "Tassa mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā bhisakkaṃ sallakattaṃ upaṭṭhāpeyyuṃ. "
msgstr "Their friends and colleagues, relatives and kin would get a field surgeon to treat them. "

msgctxt "mn105:19.3"
msgid "Tassa so bhisakko sallakatto satthena vaṇamukhaṃ parikanteyya. "
msgstr "The surgeon would cut open the wound with a scalpel, "

msgctxt "mn105:19.4"
msgid "Satthena vaṇamukhaṃ parikantitvā esaniyā sallaṃ eseyya. "
msgstr "probe for the arrow, "

msgctxt "mn105:19.5"
msgid "Esaniyā sallaṃ esitvā sallaṃ abbuheyya, apaneyya visadosaṃ saupādisesaṃ. "
msgstr "extract it, and expel the poison, leaving some residue behind. "

# NOTE: See BB’s note on why anupa-is to be preferred here. See also Analayo, Comparative Study, p 611 note 136 “SHT IV 500 folio 3V 3 reads [sā]va[ś]eṣaṃ nira[va](śe)ṣaṃ (iti manyamānaḥ); cf. also SHT X 3274V 3”
#. VAR: Saupādisesoti → anupādisesoti (s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: jānamāno → maññamāno (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn105:19.6"
msgid "Saupādisesoti jānamāno so evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "Thinking that no residue remained, the surgeon would say: "

#. VAR: saupādiseso → anupādiseso (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn105:19.7"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, ubbhataṃ kho te sallaṃ, apanīto visadoso saupādiseso. "
msgstr "‘My good man, the dart has been extracted and the poison expelled without residue. "

msgctxt "mn105:19.8"
msgid "Analañca te antarāyāya. "
msgstr "It’s not capable of harming you. "

msgctxt "mn105:19.9"
msgid "Sappāyāni ceva bhojanāni bhuñjeyyāsi, mā te asappāyāni bhojanāni bhuñjato vaṇo assāvī assa. "
msgstr "Eat only suitable food. Don’t eat unsuitable food, or else the wound may get infected. "

msgctxt "mn105:19.10"
msgid "Kālena kālañca vaṇaṃ dhoveyyāsi, kālena kālaṃ vaṇamukhaṃ ālimpeyyāsi, mā te na kālena kālaṃ vaṇaṃ dhovato na kālena kālaṃ vaṇamukhaṃ ālimpato pubbalohitaṃ vaṇamukhaṃ pariyonandhi. "
msgstr "Regularly wash the wound and anoint the opening, or else it’ll get covered with pus and blood. "

msgctxt "mn105:19.11"
msgid "Mā ca vātātape cārittaṃ anuyuñji, mā te vātātape cārittaṃ anuyuttassa rajosūkaṃ vaṇamukhaṃ anuddhaṃsesi. "
msgstr "Don’t walk too much in the wind and sun, or else dust and dirt will infect the wound. "

#. VAR: vaṇasāropī’ti → vaṇassāropīti (mr)
msgctxt "mn105:19.12"
msgid "Vaṇānurakkhī ca, ambho purisa, vihareyyāsi vaṇasāropī’ti. "
msgstr "Take care of the wound, my good sir, heal it.’ "

