#. REF: nya28, pts-vp-pli2.261, sc17
msgctxt "mn105:28.1"
msgid "So vata, sunakkhatta, bhikkhu chasu phassāyatanesu saṃvutakārī ‘upadhi dukkhassa mūlan’ti—"
msgstr "Truly, Sunakkhatta, that mendicant practices restraint regarding the six fields of contact. "

msgctxt "mn105:28.2"
msgid "iti viditvā nirupadhi upadhisaṅkhaye vimutto upadhismiṃ vā kāyaṃ upasaṃharissati cittaṃ vā uppādessatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "Understanding that attachment is the root of suffering, they are freed with the ending of attachments. It’s not possible that they would apply their body or interest their mind in any attachment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya29
msgctxt "mn105:29.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, sunakkhatta, āpānīyakaṃso vaṇṇasampanno gandhasampanno rasasampanno; "
msgstr "Suppose there was a bronze cup of beverage that had a nice color, aroma, and flavor. "

msgctxt "mn105:29.2"
msgid "so ca kho visena saṃsaṭṭho. "
msgstr "But it was mixed with poison. "

msgctxt "mn105:29.3"
msgid "Atha puriso āgaccheyya jīvitukāmo amaritukāmo sukhakāmo dukkhapaṭikūlo. "
msgstr "Then a person would come along who wants to live and doesn’t want to die, who wants to be happy and recoils from pain. "

msgctxt "mn105:29.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, sunakkhatta, "
msgstr "What do you think, Sunakkhatta? "

msgctxt "mn105:29.5"
msgid "api nu so puriso amuṃ āpānīyakaṃsaṃ piveyya yaṃ jaññā: "
msgstr "Would that person drink that beverage knowing that "

msgctxt "mn105:29.6"
msgid "‘imāhaṃ pivitvā maraṇaṃ vā nigacchāmi maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhan’”ti? "
msgstr "it would result in death or deadly suffering?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn105:29.7"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn105:29.8"
msgid "“Evameva kho, sunakkhatta, so vata bhikkhu chasu phassāyatanesu saṃvutakārī ‘upadhi dukkhassa mūlan’ti—"
msgstr "“In the same way, Sunakkhatta, that mendicant practices restraint regarding the six fields of contact. "

msgctxt "mn105:29.9"
msgid "iti viditvā nirupadhi upadhisaṅkhaye vimutto upadhismiṃ vā kāyaṃ upasaṃharissati cittaṃ vā uppādessatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "Understanding that attachment is the root of suffering, they are freed with the ending of attachments. It’s not possible that they would apply their body or interest their mind in any attachment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya30, sc18
#. VAR: āsīviso → āsiviso (s1, mr)
msgctxt "mn105:30.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, sunakkhatta, āsīviso ghoraviso. "
msgstr "Suppose there was a lethal viper. "

msgctxt "mn105:30.2"
msgid "Atha puriso āgaccheyya jīvitukāmo amaritukāmo sukhakāmo dukkhapaṭikūlo. "
msgstr "Then a person would come along who wants to live and doesn’t want to die, who wants to be happy and recoils from pain. "

msgctxt "mn105:30.3"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, sunakkhatta, "
msgstr "What do you think, Sunakkhatta? "

#. VAR: dajjā → yuñjeyya (bj, mr)
msgctxt "mn105:30.4"
msgid "api nu so puriso amussa āsīvisassa ghoravisassa hatthaṃ vā aṅguṭṭhaṃ vā dajjā yaṃ jaññā: "
msgstr "Would that person give that lethal viper their hand or finger knowing that "

msgctxt "mn105:30.5"
msgid "‘imināhaṃ daṭṭho maraṇaṃ vā nigacchāmi maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhan’”ti? "
msgstr "it would result in death or deadly suffering?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn105:30.6"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn105:30.7"
msgid "“Evameva kho, sunakkhatta, so vata bhikkhu chasu phassāyatanesu saṃvutakārī ‘upadhi dukkhassa mūlan’ti—"
msgstr "“In the same way, Sunakkhatta, that mendicant practices restraint regarding the six fields of contact. "

msgctxt "mn105:30.8"
msgid "iti viditvā nirupadhi upadhisaṅkhaye vimutto upadhismiṃ vā kāyaṃ upasaṃharissati cittaṃ vā uppādessatīti—"
msgstr "Understanding that attachment is the root of suffering, they are freed with the ending of attachments. It’s not possible that they would apply their body or interest their mind in any attachment.” "

msgctxt "mn105:30.9"
msgid "netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "mn105:30.10"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "mn105:30.11"
msgid "Attamano sunakkhatto licchaviputto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, Sunakkhatta of the Licchavi clan was happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn105:30.12"
msgid "Sunakkhattasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

